The composite SVRGIS information is made available to the public primarily in .zip files of approximately 50MB size.  The files located at the access point contain track information regarding known tornados during the period 1950 to 2006.   Although available to all, the data provided may be of particular value to weather professionals and students of meteorological sciences.  An instructional manual is provided on how to build and develop a basic severe weather report GIS database in ArcGis and is located at the technical documentation site contained in this metadata
